{
  "texts": [
    "• \"vacuous bounds are certainly better than no bounds at all!\"",
    "This opinion is a little cynical, it can be rephrased as \"better have a theory that doesn't work than no theory at all: at least we can claim we have a theory, and some people might even believe us\".",
    "But the theory just says nothing.",
    "• \"let's get back to work, and improve the bounds\".",
    "Since the publication of the first PAC-Bayes bounds already mentioned (Shawe-Taylor and Williamson, 1997; McAllester, 1998; McAllester, 1999), many variants were proven."
  ]
}